Defendant Deontez Woods in court with attorney David Herring.  Joy Hammond appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.  

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  Defendant sentenced to serve 6 months  in the House of Correction.  Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on Probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 1 year.
Conditions: 
*  Possess no guns;
*  AODA assessment/treatment deemed appropriate;
*  Maintain absolute sobriety;
*  Maintain employment;
*  Perform 30 hours of community service;
*  Pay all costs and surcharges or, if not paid, convert to a civil judgment;
*  Submit a DNA sample and pay the DNA surcharge.

If the defendant successfully completes all conditions of probation (costs and surcharges excluded), Court will grant expungement.  Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief received and filed.
